Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{700%grams} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide chips (no need to peel).

Pop onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> Use two baking trays if necessary.

When hot, roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{30-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, remove the @confit duck legs{2} from their packaging. Place onto a lined baking tray, skin-side up, and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Roast on the middle shelf of your oven for ~{25-30%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Ensure the duck is piping hot throughout.

While everything cooks, halve, peel and slice the @red onion{1/2}(sliced as thinly as you can). Pop it into a #small bowl{} with the @rice vinegar{15%milliliter} and @sugar{1%tsp}(for the pickle). Add a pinch of @salt{}, mix together, then set your pickled onion aside.

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips, then chop into roughly 1cm pieces.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Crush the @salted peanuts{25%grams} in the unopened sachet using a #rolling pin{}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the chopped pepper and stir-fry until slightly charred, ~{4-5%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then add the garlic and @Chinese five spice{1%sachet}.

> Add less Chinese Five Spice if you'd prefer things milder.

Stir and cook for ~{1-2%minutes}, then remove from the heat and transfer the spicy seasoning to a #bowl{}.

Once the duck is cooked, transfer to a #plate{}. Use two #forks{} to shred the duck as finely as you can. Discard the bones.

Pop your (now empty) frying pan back on medium heat and add the shredded duck and @teriyaki sauce{75%grams}. Stir together and cook until piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}. Remove from the heat.

Once the chips are cooked, remove them from the oven and add the spicy seasoning (as much as you'd like) to the baking tray, mixing everything together.

Share the spicy chips between your plates and top with the teriyaki duck.

Scatter over the pickled onion and peanuts, then tuck in. Enjoy!